
[1]conjunctive

   CONJUNCTIVE, a.

   1. Closely united.

   2. Uniting; serving to unite.

   3. In grammar, the conjunctive mode is that which follows a
   conjunction, or expresses some condition, or contingency. It is more
   generally called subjunctive.
